419
00:24:13.911 --> 00:24:18.207
<i>Awaiting the timeless</i>
<i>times of nirvana.</i>

420
00:24:18.248 --> 00:24:20.125
<i>- Maurice</i>
<i>was doing the hustling.</i>

421
00:24:20.209 --> 00:24:22.044
<i>pushing us out there.</i>

422
00:24:22.127 --> 00:24:25.547
<i>Eventually. we got a contract</i>
<i>with Warner Brothers.</i>

423
00:24:25.631 --> 00:24:28.926
<i>We call on you because we</i>

424
00:24:29.009 --> 00:24:34.139
<i>love you.</i>

425
00:24:37.393 --> 00:24:39.144
<i>- We were playing</i>
<i>Black colleges.</i>

426
00:24:39.228 --> 00:24:40.854
We were a college group first.

427
00:24:43.023 --> 00:24:48.237
At the time. I was in the
band called Friends & Love.

428
00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:50.447
<i>We opened for</i>
<i>Earth. Wind & Fire.</i>

429
00:24:50.531 --> 00:24:52.199
I had never heard
no Black people

430
00:24:52.282 --> 00:24:54.159
playing no music like that.

431
00:24:56.120 --> 00:24:59.581
Dressed like little
jazz geek kids. you know.

432
00:24:59.623 --> 00:25:01.667
looked up to him because it
was harmonically complex

433
00:25:01.750 --> 00:25:04.294
and exciting and orchestrated.

434
00:25:04.378 --> 00:25:05.671
And it was just banging.

435
00:25:08.924 --> 00:25:10.426
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

436
00:25:10.467 --> 00:25:12.094
<i>We were a niche band.</i>

437
00:25:12.136 --> 00:25:15.014
<i>but we weren't connecting</i>
<i>with the wider audience</i>

438
00:25:15.097 --> 00:25:16.724
<i>that Maurice wanted.</i>

439
00:25:21.186 --> 00:25:23.772
<i>We didn't sell very well.</i>

440
00:25:23.856 --> 00:25:25.941
<i>The record companies</i>
<i>didn't know what to do with us</i>

441
00:25:26.025 --> 00:25:30.279
<i>because we wasn't your usual</i>
<i>R&B Black band.</i>

442
00:25:30.362 --> 00:25:32.239
<i>- We struggled</i>
<i>for about 18 months.</i>

443
00:25:32.322 --> 00:25:34.324
<i>trying to get it together.</i>

444
00:25:34.408 --> 00:25:37.453
There was some resentment
being built.

445
00:25:37.494 --> 00:25:39.121
<i>When we gonna get</i>
<i>some more work.</i>

446
00:25:39.163 --> 00:25:41.040
<i>so we can make some money?</i>

447
00:25:41.123 --> 00:25:43.792
Some of the guys were much
older with the attitude.

448
00:25:43.876 --> 00:25:48.839
well. look. I know as much
as you do. business-wise.

449
00:25:48.922 --> 00:25:52.092
I don't think they wanted
Maurice to be the leader.

450
00:25:52.176 --> 00:25:55.179
I think that was
a problem amongst them.

451
00:25:55.262 --> 00:25:58.140
They all wanted to be
the leader. you know.

452
00:25:58.223 --> 00:26:00.059
<i>But it was Maurice's group.</i>

453
00:26:25.584 --> 00:26:28.670
We were called
into a meeting.

454
00:26:28.754 --> 00:26:32.758
and everything
was up in smoke.

455
00:26:32.841 --> 00:26:37.304
<i>What I noticed.</i>
<i>Verdine wasn't there.</i>

456
00:26:37.387 --> 00:26:40.349
and Maurice wasn't there.

457
00:26:41.767 --> 00:26:45.562
Maurice did not
like confrontation.

458
00:26:45.646 --> 00:26:49.108
He did not like
uncomfortable conversations.

459
00:26:49.191 --> 00:26:50.692
He--

460
00:26:50.734 --> 00:26:53.695
He was chickenshit.

461
00:26:53.779 --> 00:26:56.198
You know.
that's just the truth.

462
00:26:56.240 --> 00:27:00.119
<i>We heard we were no longer</i>
<i>a member of this group.</i>

463
00:27:00.202 --> 00:27:02.704
Well. I couldn't think
straight because. I mean.

464
00:27:02.788 --> 00:27:05.999
this is my brother.

465
00:27:06.083 --> 00:27:08.877
<i>Man. what kind of nonsense</i>
<i>is that. you know?</i>

466
00:27:08.919 --> 00:27:11.755
<i>Reese is gonna get rid</i>
<i>of all of us.</i>

467
00:27:15.759 --> 00:27:18.554
He would say
to me things like.

468
00:27:18.637 --> 00:27:20.472
people are in your life
for a season.

469
00:27:20.556 --> 00:27:23.142
and when it's over. it's--

470
00:27:31.567 --> 00:27:34.611
<i>- Start by focusing</i>
<i>in your heart.</i>

471
00:27:34.695 --> 00:27:37.239
<i>Breathe in the energy</i>
<i>of the universe.</i>

472
00:27:37.281 --> 00:27:39.950
<i>the shakti of the universe.</i>

473
00:27:41.827 --> 00:27:45.497
<i>- The first band didn't</i>
<i>come together. you know.</i>

474
00:27:45.581 --> 00:27:48.750
<i>But I wasn't ready to give up.</i>

475
00:27:48.792 --> 00:27:50.919
<i>Let it fill your whole body.</i>

476
00:27:51.003 --> 00:27:54.756
<i>He believed in his dream.</i>

477
00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:58.427
He would visualize.
visualize. visualize...

478
00:28:00.721 --> 00:28:03.724
<i>Writing down affirmations</i>

479
00:28:03.807 --> 00:28:06.435
up until 1:00. 2:00
in the morning.

480
00:28:14.568 --> 00:28:16.361
<i>- I just wanted</i>
<i>a younger approach.</i>

481
00:28:16.445 --> 00:28:18.864
<i>more commercial approach.</i>

482
00:28:18.947 --> 00:28:21.325
<i>a new sound. a new energy.</i>

483
00:28:21.408 --> 00:28:24.244
<i>Verdine was the first person.</i>

484
00:28:24.328 --> 00:28:27.873
We solidified. I'm keeping
this dude in the group.

485
00:28:27.956 --> 00:28:31.043
<i>- I got Ralph.</i>
<i>hired him as a drummer.</i>

486
00:28:31.126 --> 00:28:33.253
<i>- They had seen me play</i>
<i>at a club</i>

487
00:28:33.337 --> 00:28:34.796
<i>called Maverick's Flat.</i>

488
00:28:34.838 --> 00:28:36.840
When the opportunity
comes about. man.

489
00:28:36.924 --> 00:28:40.761
you walk into something that
totally changes your life.

490
00:28:40.844 --> 00:28:43.805
<i>- I just put it together.</i>
<i>piece by piece.</i>

491
00:28:47.226 --> 00:28:48.810
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

492
00:28:48.852 --> 00:28:51.104
This is Phil Bailey.

493
00:28:51.146 --> 00:28:52.648
- What sign are you. brother?
- I'm a Taurus.

494
00:28:52.731 --> 00:28:54.650
Taurus. the bull. Right on.

495
00:28:54.691 --> 00:28:56.568
<i>It was divine destiny</i>

496
00:28:56.652 --> 00:29:01.573
to join a group
that I already admired.

497
00:29:01.657 --> 00:29:03.492
Maurice White is
the leader of the group.

498
00:29:03.575 --> 00:29:05.869
so like the pilot of our ship.

499
00:29:05.953 --> 00:29:08.330
<i>- Being a leader.</i>
<i>you have to be able to. like.</i>

500
00:29:08.372 --> 00:29:10.415
<i>keep it on a good level.</i>

501
00:29:10.499 --> 00:29:12.751
<i>I always try to be an example.</i>

502
00:29:12.834 --> 00:29:15.003
Reese was
ten years older than us.

503
00:29:15.087 --> 00:29:18.507
<i>We were learning</i>
<i>so many things</i>

504
00:29:18.590 --> 00:29:21.468
<i>because we're. like.</i>
<i>21 years old.</i>

505
00:29:21.551 --> 00:29:24.388
<i>It's our first rodeo.</i>

506
00:29:24.471 --> 00:29:28.517
Incense for $1. 25 of them.

507
00:29:30.978 --> 00:29:35.774
We were anxious to see where
Maurice was gonna take this.

508
00:29:39.695 --> 00:29:43.198
<i>- There was a circuit that</i>
<i>the artists would travel--</i>

509
00:29:43.240 --> 00:29:48.245
<i>the Regal. the Howard.</i>
<i>the Apollo. the Uptown.</i>

510
00:29:48.328 --> 00:29:51.123
<i>There's a bunch of theaters</i>
<i>that's a little hostile.</i>

511
00:29:51.206 --> 00:29:53.709
<i>And if you wasn't great.</i>
<i>the audience would boo you</i>

512
00:29:53.750 --> 00:29:56.211
<i>and throw you off the stage.</i>

513
00:29:56.295 --> 00:29:59.798
<i>- I remember playing there</i>
<i>with the Commodores.</i>

514
00:29:59.881 --> 00:30:04.344
They're going to give you
an opportunity to present.

515
00:30:04.428 --> 00:30:07.723
What they're not gonna do
is lie to you.

516
00:30:07.764 --> 00:30:10.225
<i>Only the strong's</i>
<i>gonna survive.</i>

517
00:30:10.267 --> 00:30:13.854
One day. we get a chance
to go to Philadelphia.

518
00:30:13.937 --> 00:30:18.442
and we're doing
the Uptown Theatre.

519
00:30:21.194 --> 00:30:25.324
<i>The revue is</i>
<i>five doo-wop groups</i>

520
00:30:25.407 --> 00:30:27.993
<i>and Earth. Wind & Fire.</i>

521
00:30:29.453 --> 00:30:31.955
<i>These groups had on</i>
<i>tailor-made suits</i>

522
00:30:32.039 --> 00:30:34.791
cut to the nines.
everybody looking tight.

523
00:30:34.875 --> 00:30:37.085
everybody looking alike.

524
00:30:37.127 --> 00:30:42.215
<i>That's what was expected</i>
<i>at the Uptown.</i>

525
00:30:42.299 --> 00:30:43.717
Although we were cool.
we were different.

526
00:30:45.594 --> 00:30:47.596
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Yeah. what about the... ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

527
00:30:47.679 --> 00:30:51.433
With afros. no shirts.

528
00:30:51.516 --> 00:30:54.936
wearing dashikis and Capezios.

529
00:30:54.978 --> 00:30:56.313
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Hey. hey ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

530
00:30:59.107 --> 00:31:00.984
<i>We were outsiders.</i>

531
00:31:01.068 --> 00:31:03.945
<i>They were going to hate us.</i>

532
00:31:10.285 --> 00:31:12.746
<i>Oh. I was scared to death.</i>

533
00:31:12.829 --> 00:31:15.832
<i>scared out of my wits.</i>
<i>you know?</i>

534
00:31:15.916 --> 00:31:19.878
Maurice thought.
I'm gonna defy the odds.

535
00:31:22.923 --> 00:31:29.596
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

536
00:31:29.679 --> 00:31:33.517
<i>He tells all of us the plan.</i>

537
00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:34.559
It's a bold move.

538
00:31:37.062 --> 00:31:39.815
<i>Acts have gone on before us.</i>

539
00:31:39.856 --> 00:31:41.942
<i>It was time for us to go up.</i>

540
00:31:43.360 --> 00:31:46.071
<i>We got a new group</i>
<i>from California.</i>

541
00:31:46.154 --> 00:31:47.948
Earth. Wind & Fire.

542
00:31:49.574 --> 00:31:54.204
<i>People's mouth open.</i>
<i>and then you got laughter.</i>

543
00:31:56.373 --> 00:32:00.168
So Maurice says.
sit down on the floor.

544
00:32:00.252 --> 00:32:02.879
Sit down
in the lotus position.

545
00:32:02.963 --> 00:32:05.006
We got in the lotus
position. folded our legs.

546
00:32:05.048 --> 00:32:07.050
man. and we just meditated.

547
00:32:11.012 --> 00:32:13.098
And they were just
looking at us crazy.

548
00:32:13.181 --> 00:32:15.851
Minute one.
what are you thinking?

549
00:32:15.934 --> 00:32:18.270
I'm too scared to think.

550
00:32:18.353 --> 00:32:20.856
I'm going. okay. now.
this is either gonna work

551
00:32:20.897 --> 00:32:23.525
or this is gonna be
a total disaster.

552
00:32:23.608 --> 00:32:27.195
You have cups and stuff
thrown up there on the stage.

553
00:32:27.279 --> 00:32:29.156
Get them guys off the stage!
Get them out of there.

554
00:32:29.239 --> 00:32:30.574
<i>Get them out of there.</i>

555
00:32:33.201 --> 00:32:34.453
We're sitting there
looking like this.

556
00:32:34.536 --> 00:32:37.080
so one eye like this.
and oh. my God.

557
00:32:38.498 --> 00:32:40.584
<i>- Three minutes</i>
<i>into that mission.</i>

558
00:32:40.667 --> 00:32:41.751
<i>what are you thinking?</i>

559
00:32:41.835 --> 00:32:44.379
Now the heart's
beating fast.

560
00:32:44.421 --> 00:32:46.298
<i>The mouth is dry.</i>

561
00:32:46.381 --> 00:32:48.133
We sat there and looked
at that audience

562
00:32:48.216 --> 00:32:51.636
for at least five minutes.

563
00:32:51.720 --> 00:32:53.054
Six. seven. eight minutes.

564
00:32:56.308 --> 00:33:01.229
Finally. it calmed down
just enough.

565
00:33:01.313 --> 00:33:04.483
<i>- I guess they</i>
<i>got tired of heckling us.</i>

566
00:33:04.566 --> 00:33:08.612
<i>and Maurice starts</i>
<i>playing the kalimba.</i>

567
00:33:15.327 --> 00:33:17.370
He tells me to get
on the congas.

568
00:33:19.706 --> 00:33:23.043
Then he tells over to Ralph.
start a groove.

569
00:33:25.879 --> 00:33:27.756
And then bass line.

570
00:33:34.971 --> 00:33:36.556
And then we went.

571
00:34:06.294 --> 00:34:07.879
We started hearing
people clap a little bit.

572
00:34:07.963 --> 00:34:11.383
<i>Yeah. that's the fire.</i>
<i>the fire.</i>

573
00:34:11.466 --> 00:34:13.385
And then
we proceeded to kill.

574
00:34:33.113 --> 00:34:35.991
<i>- Sometimes people</i>
<i>are afraid of change.</i>

575
00:34:36.032 --> 00:34:37.867
Through all of that.
they won them over

576
00:34:37.951 --> 00:34:39.369
with a new experience.

577
00:34:47.711 --> 00:34:50.714
<i>- Maurice said. this is</i>
<i>the day that we found out</i>

578
00:34:50.797 --> 00:34:52.299
<i>that we got something.</i>

579
00:34:52.340 --> 00:34:57.679
That was an endorsement
to do what he was saying

580
00:34:57.762 --> 00:35:00.181
<i>philosophically and musically.</i>

581
00:35:01.349 --> 00:35:04.728
To lead a band
of Black guys. right.

582
00:35:04.811 --> 00:35:09.608
you know. of cats.
you gotta be really tough.

583
00:35:09.691 --> 00:35:11.234
<i>And Maurice was tough.</i>

584
00:35:14.571 --> 00:35:18.241
<i>We had something big</i>
<i>to accomplish. you know?</i>

585
00:35:18.325 --> 00:35:20.285
<i>- I get a call</i>
<i>from Maurice White.</i>

586
00:35:20.368 --> 00:35:23.872
<i>And he tells me</i>
<i>he's got a group.</i>

587
00:35:23.913 --> 00:35:27.709
So I go and I see
Earth. Wind & Fire.

588
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:29.210
<i>This is good stuff.</i>

589
00:35:29.294 --> 00:35:32.589
I thought. this could be
a successful band.

590
00:35:32.672 --> 00:35:37.218
<i>Jim Brown has them. but Reese</i>
<i>wanted different management.</i>

591
00:35:37.302 --> 00:35:40.388
So I said.
I'd like to manage you.

592
00:35:40.430 --> 00:35:43.767
<i>Maurice brought the band</i>
<i>out to my house</i>

593
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:46.227
<i>to sign the contract.</i>

594
00:35:46.311 --> 00:35:48.897
I said to him. why did you
bring everybody?

595
00:35:48.980 --> 00:35:51.733
I'm only signing you.

596
00:35:51.775 --> 00:35:55.528
<i>I believe these kids were</i>
<i>part of Maurice's vision</i>

597
00:35:55.612 --> 00:35:58.615
but not the cause of it.
the impetus of it.

598
00:35:58.698 --> 00:36:00.575
It was him.

599
00:36:00.659 --> 00:36:04.037
<i>Then I put together a deal</i>
<i>with Columbia Records.</i>

600
00:36:04.120 --> 00:36:07.916
<i>with Clive Davis.</i>

601
00:36:07.957 --> 00:36:11.503
<i>- When people like Clive Davis</i>
<i>comes into your life.</i>

602
00:36:11.586 --> 00:36:15.090
it's giving you the major
opportunity to. like. be big.

603
00:36:15.131 --> 00:36:17.300
<i>The first experience</i>
<i>of recording</i>

604
00:36:17.384 --> 00:36:20.011
<i>that we all did together was</i>
<i>the "Last Days and Time."</i>

605
00:36:20.095 --> 00:36:21.888
<i>then "Head to the Sky."</i>

606
00:36:30.230 --> 00:36:34.401
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Evil running
through our brain ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

607
00:36:34.442 --> 00:36:38.488
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ We and evil is about
the same. oh. Lord ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

608
00:36:40.156 --> 00:36:45.870
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Well. yeah ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

609
00:36:45.954 --> 00:36:48.248
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Ooh. yeah ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

610
00:36:48.331 --> 00:36:50.375
<i>I was a little bit shy</i>
<i>in the beginning.</i>

611
00:36:50.458 --> 00:36:53.294
<i>But after I discovered</i>
<i>a sound for myself.</i>

612
00:36:53.378 --> 00:36:55.255
<i>I was a whole</i>
<i>different personality.</i>

613
00:36:55.338 --> 00:36:59.175
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Yeah. evil ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

614
00:36:59.259 --> 00:37:01.469
<i>For the band.</i>
<i>what we try to do</i>

615
00:37:01.511 --> 00:37:05.014
is to bring the nine together
as one.

616
00:37:05.098 --> 00:37:06.558
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Oh. oh. oh. oh ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

617
00:37:06.641 --> 00:37:08.476
<i>- Maurice definitely</i>
<i>had a vision.</i>

618
00:37:08.518 --> 00:37:12.731
and he let us express
ourselves very freely.

619
00:37:12.814 --> 00:37:18.153
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Yeah. well. well ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

620
00:37:35.211 --> 00:37:37.964
There was always
a book to read.

621
00:37:38.047 --> 00:37:39.048
We would stay up
late at night

622
00:37:39.132 --> 00:37:41.050
and talk about everything--

623
00:37:41.134 --> 00:37:42.218
cosmic consciousness.

624
00:37:42.302 --> 00:37:44.345
Spirituality. metaphysics.

625
00:37:44.429 --> 00:37:46.306
Everyone else
in the group got into

626
00:37:46.389 --> 00:37:51.936
transcendental meditation.
positive self-betterment.

627
00:37:57.692 --> 00:37:59.861
Maurice had
a lot of elixirs.

628
00:37:59.903 --> 00:38:00.987
so many drops in the water.

629
00:38:01.070 --> 00:38:03.531
<i>and supplements</i>
<i>and all of that.</i>

630
00:38:03.615 --> 00:38:06.534
We have one
of his green juice recipes.

631
00:38:06.618 --> 00:38:07.619
Oh. wow.

632
00:38:10.705 --> 00:38:12.290
<i>Items--greens.</i>

633
00:38:12.373 --> 00:38:13.917
This is intense.

634
00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:17.420
<i>Sunflower seeds. pumpkin</i>
<i>seeds. spotted bananas.</i>

635
00:38:17.504 --> 00:38:18.379
so they gotta be ripe.

636
