<i>is Earth. Wind & Fire.</i>

1020
00:58:13.699 --> 00:58:16.410
<i>- The first Grammy</i>
<i>was quite a thing. you know.</i>

1021
00:58:16.451 --> 00:58:18.120
<i>It's something</i>
<i>that you live for.</i>

1022
00:58:18.203 --> 00:58:21.373
As we got bigger musically.
we got bigger personnel-wise.

1023
00:58:22.958 --> 00:58:25.085
Reese wanted to get a horn
section because the sound

1024
00:58:25.168 --> 00:58:26.920
had expanded so much.

1025
00:58:27.004 --> 00:58:29.047
<i>So we brought</i>
<i>the Phenix Horns...</i>

1026
00:58:29.131 --> 00:58:30.590
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Let's meet today ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1027
00:58:30.674 --> 00:58:31.675
<i>Which was Don Myrick...</i>

1028
00:58:31.758 --> 00:58:33.301
<i>- He plays so beautiful.</i>
<i>don't you agree?</i>

1029
00:58:33.385 --> 00:58:34.845
<i>Louis Satterfield...</i>

1030
00:58:34.928 --> 00:58:39.057
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Yeah ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1031
00:58:39.141 --> 00:58:40.726
<i>Rahmlee Michael Davis</i>

1032
00:58:40.809 --> 00:58:43.770
<i>and Michael Harris--</i>

1033
00:58:43.854 --> 00:58:46.857
<i>four horns.</i>
<i>like a Mack truck. man.</i>

1034
00:58:51.361 --> 00:58:53.280
<i>- We were having</i>
<i>a really good run.</i>

1035
00:58:53.321 --> 00:58:54.990
<i>There was a period there</i>
<i>where everything we touched</i>

1036
00:58:55.073 --> 00:58:55.949
<i>turned to gold.</i>

1037
00:59:01.371 --> 00:59:04.541
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1038
00:59:04.624 --> 00:59:07.127
Okay. that smile. That's it.

1039
00:59:07.210 --> 00:59:12.674
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1040
00:59:12.758 --> 00:59:16.428
<i>- We started recording</i>
<i>the next album. "Spirit."</i>

1041
00:59:16.470 --> 00:59:18.847
We were doing big arrangements
on the record.

1042
00:59:18.930 --> 00:59:22.434
<i>beautifully arranged</i>
<i>by Charles Stepney.</i>

1043
00:59:22.517 --> 00:59:25.145
You know. man.
we were in it then.

1044
00:59:25.187 --> 00:59:27.355
<i>- ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Shining down</i>
<i>its harvest light ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1045
00:59:27.439 --> 00:59:28.899
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Music all around... ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1046
00:59:28.982 --> 00:59:31.568
But then Maurice got
a phone call in the studio

1047
00:59:31.651 --> 00:59:33.070
saying that Charles
had just passed.

1048
00:59:36.198 --> 00:59:38.492
<i>He had a heart attack.</i>

1049
00:59:38.533 --> 00:59:40.702
<i>Yeah. just out</i>
<i>of the blue. boom.</i>

1050
00:59:40.786 --> 00:59:42.996
<i>He was out of here.</i>

1051
00:59:43.080 --> 00:59:45.624
<i>I couldn't believe it.</i>
<i>you know.</i>

1052
00:59:45.707 --> 00:59:47.334
It was like
he was in wonderment.

1053
00:59:47.417 --> 00:59:48.418
like. how could this be?

1054
00:59:48.502 --> 00:59:49.961
I just talked to him.

1055
00:59:50.045 --> 00:59:53.548
And one minute he's there.
and then you're not?

1056
00:59:53.632 --> 00:59:55.634
<i>- It affected me</i>
<i>very deeply. you know.</i>

1057
00:59:55.717 --> 00:59:58.178
<i>I was very emotional.</i>

1058
00:59:58.220 --> 01:00:01.556
My dad. he had triggers.

1059
01:00:01.640 --> 01:00:05.393
<i>Charles dying</i>
<i>brought up past trauma.</i>

1060
01:00:11.733 --> 01:00:14.861
<i>- Back then.</i>
<i>where he grew up in Memphis.</i>

1061
01:00:14.903 --> 01:00:16.905
it was a rarity of having
a father in the house.

1062
01:00:18.406 --> 01:00:22.786
<i>- Maurice's father</i>
<i>was John White.</i>

1063
01:00:22.869 --> 01:00:27.332
<i>He was absent during most</i>
<i>of Maurice's childhood.</i>

1064
01:00:27.374 --> 01:00:32.879
<i>He owned a nightclub and was</i>
<i>part of that music scene.</i>

1065
01:00:32.963 --> 01:00:37.592
But he was also
this gangster figure.

1066
01:00:37.676 --> 01:00:39.594
<i>From what I understand.</i>

1067
01:00:39.678 --> 01:00:41.388
one day he went into
one of his establishments.

1068
01:00:41.429 --> 01:00:47.811
and somebody who was not
his same skin color shot him.

1069
01:00:49.771 --> 01:00:53.984
<i>- He is killed before Maurice</i>
<i>is five years old.</i>

1070
01:00:56.903 --> 01:01:00.740
<i>- When he talked</i>
<i>about his life as a child.</i>

1071
01:01:00.824 --> 01:01:03.076
his knee would go--tschoo--

1072
01:01:03.160 --> 01:01:04.119
like that.

1073
01:01:08.206 --> 01:01:12.836
<i>After Charles passed.</i>
<i>it was hard for him to accept.</i>

1074
01:01:12.919 --> 01:01:14.588
But the world doesn't care

1075
01:01:14.671 --> 01:01:17.382
who's gone
and who is not gone.

1076
01:01:17.465 --> 01:01:20.886
It just keeps on rolling.

1077
01:01:20.969 --> 01:01:25.015
<i>Maurice learned almost</i>
<i>everything from Charles.</i>

1078
01:01:25.098 --> 01:01:28.018
Maurice was like. oh. my God.

1079
01:01:28.101 --> 01:01:29.144
Now what do I do?

1080
01:01:45.118 --> 01:01:49.789
<i>- I started studying</i>
<i>Egyptology.</i>

1081
01:01:49.873 --> 01:01:54.377
<i>I went into the pyramids</i>
<i>just to meditate.</i>

1082
01:01:54.461 --> 01:01:57.756
<i>It gave me new energy.</i>
<i>and I was able to evolve</i>

1083
01:01:57.839 --> 01:02:00.133
<i>into a different person.</i>

1084
01:02:00.175 --> 01:02:04.012
<i>It seemed like I was getting</i>
<i>help from the other side.</i>

1085
01:02:04.095 --> 01:02:06.306
<i>I was just fascinated</i>
<i>with the whole thing.</i>

1086
01:02:06.348 --> 01:02:09.267
<i>the artistic value of Egypt.</i>

1087
01:02:09.309 --> 01:02:12.520
<i>the contributions</i>
<i>that they made to society.</i>

1088
01:02:12.604 --> 01:02:14.856
Look at how the pyramids
were built.

1089
01:02:14.940 --> 01:02:16.900
with the science
and the technology.

1090
01:02:16.983 --> 01:02:21.071
<i>They are humanity</i>
<i>at its finest.</i>

1091
01:02:21.154 --> 01:02:26.076
<i>Maurice begins learning</i>
<i>about Afrofuturism.</i>

1092
01:02:26.159 --> 01:02:29.996
<i>the idea that these ancient</i>
<i>civilizations are not</i>

1093
01:02:30.038 --> 01:02:33.583
just symbols of
Black people's past.

1094
01:02:33.667 --> 01:02:38.255
<i>they are also the future</i>
<i>and the infinite possibilities</i>

1095
01:02:38.338 --> 01:02:42.008
<i>that exist throughout</i>
<i>the universe.</i>

1096
01:02:42.050 --> 01:02:44.844
<i>the concept of space travel.</i>

1097
01:02:44.928 --> 01:02:49.808
<i>the existence of beings</i>
<i>on other planets.</i>

1098
01:02:49.891 --> 01:02:52.060
<i>- The whole</i>
<i>space concept. aliens.</i>

1099
01:02:52.143 --> 01:02:54.729
<i>just opened up a door for me.</i>

1100
01:02:54.813 --> 01:02:56.940
My dad
talked to me sometimes

1101
01:02:57.023 --> 01:02:59.150
about astral projections.

1102
01:02:59.234 --> 01:03:00.986
<i>He was like.</i>
<i>there was one time I felt</i>

1103
01:03:01.069 --> 01:03:03.113
<i>like I was out of my body.</i>

1104
01:03:03.196 --> 01:03:04.698
He would come
back to the studio

1105
01:03:04.781 --> 01:03:08.952
with these outrageous stories
of being

1106
01:03:09.035 --> 01:03:13.498
picked up and taken in a
spaceship to another planet...

1107
01:03:16.126 --> 01:03:18.211
<i>And meeting with</i>
<i>extraterrestrials.</i>

1108
01:03:18.253 --> 01:03:20.880
And we didn't know
how to deal with this.

1109
01:03:20.922 --> 01:03:24.301
We just. you know. hey.
man. that sounds cool.

1110
01:03:28.138 --> 01:03:32.017
<i>- I saw "Close Encounters</i>
<i>of the Third Kind."</i>

1111
01:03:32.100 --> 01:03:36.896
<i>And I had a vision to write</i>
<i>the song "Fantasies."</i>

1112
01:03:36.980 --> 01:03:39.983
<i>And then all the words</i>
<i>started to come.</i>

1113
01:03:40.066 --> 01:03:42.694
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Every man has a place ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1114
01:03:42.777 --> 01:03:45.238
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ In his heart.
there's a space ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1115
01:03:45.322 --> 01:03:51.369
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ And the world can't erase
this fantasy ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1116
01:03:51.411 --> 01:03:53.663
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Take a ride in the sky ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1117
01:03:53.747 --> 01:03:56.249
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ On our ship. fantasize ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1118
01:03:56.333 --> 01:04:01.838
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ All your dreams will
come true miles away ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1119
01:04:01.921 --> 01:04:07.510
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Our voices
will ring forever ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1120
01:04:07.594 --> 01:04:12.766
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Until the 12th of never ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1121
01:04:12.849 --> 01:04:18.646
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ We all will live. love
forever ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1122
01:04:18.730 --> 01:04:24.194
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ As one ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1123
01:04:25.779 --> 01:04:26.821
<i>Everything that I had studied.</i>

1124
01:04:26.905 --> 01:04:29.949
<i>I was trying to share it</i>
<i>with the public.</i>

1125
01:04:29.991 --> 01:04:32.994
<i>so maybe it could help</i>
<i>to find themselves.</i>

1126
01:04:35.330 --> 01:04:37.707
<i>That's why.</i>
<i>on the album. "All 'N All."</i>

1127
01:04:37.791 --> 01:04:40.377
<i>it has a lot of symbols.</i>

1128
01:04:44.672 --> 01:04:46.716
<i>Through their album artwork.</i>

1129
01:04:46.800 --> 01:04:50.637
I think he was shining a light
on our history and our future

1130
01:04:50.720 --> 01:04:52.722
<i>and how it's related.</i>

1131
01:04:52.806 --> 01:04:54.641
He's inviting you
into this world.

1132
01:04:57.310 --> 01:04:59.396
<i>- We had a lot of costumes</i>
<i>that were influenced</i>

1133
01:04:59.479 --> 01:05:02.899
<i>by Africa and space.</i>

1134
01:05:02.982 --> 01:05:04.984
The real statement
wasn't really made

1135
01:05:05.026 --> 01:05:08.446
until Bill Whitten
stepped in--

1136
01:05:08.530 --> 01:05:10.615
<i>very elaborate.</i>

1137
01:05:16.746 --> 01:05:18.206
<i>We changed our whole look.</i>

1138
01:05:20.917 --> 01:05:24.087
<i>- We decided</i>
<i>to expand the show.</i>

1139
01:05:24.170 --> 01:05:27.006
<i>We wanted to more or less</i>
<i>emulate theater</i>

1140
01:05:27.090 --> 01:05:29.342
<i>in order to get</i>
<i>your attention.</i>

1141
01:05:34.556 --> 01:05:37.016
<i>- Maurice wasn't afraid</i>
<i>to spend the bread</i>

1142
01:05:37.058 --> 01:05:42.522
and contact whoever was
on the A list of entertainment

1143
01:05:42.564 --> 01:05:44.607
to help Earth. Wind & Fire.

1144
01:05:44.691 --> 01:05:48.445
And the winner is
George Faison for "The Wiz."

1145
01:05:52.240 --> 01:05:54.534
<i>- Having choreographed</i>
<i>"The Wiz."</i>

1146
01:05:54.576 --> 01:05:57.996
it was otherworldly for me.

1147
01:05:58.079 --> 01:06:00.457
<i>We had a black Dorothy.</i>

1148
01:06:00.540 --> 01:06:04.544
<i>That gave us another</i>
<i>kind of sense of pride.</i>

1149
01:06:04.627 --> 01:06:06.754
Maurice and I went to
New York to meet with George.

1150
01:06:06.838 --> 01:06:09.382
and George had all
these great ideas.

1151
01:06:09.466 --> 01:06:14.053
<i>- They asked me to stage them</i>
<i>for their next tour.</i>

1152
01:06:14.095 --> 01:06:15.346
<i>"All 'N All."</i>

1153
01:06:17.932 --> 01:06:20.894
<i>- When it came on.</i>
<i>we were great musicians.</i>

1154
01:06:20.977 --> 01:06:24.397
<i>but we wasn't organized</i>
<i>in our presentation.</i>

1155
01:06:24.481 --> 01:06:28.568
So could you tell me.
can all Black people dance?

1156
01:06:28.610 --> 01:06:30.487
No.

1157
01:06:30.570 --> 01:06:31.613
No.

1158
01:06:31.696 --> 01:06:33.573
And that's very true.

1159
01:06:35.617 --> 01:06:38.244
You trying to tell me
the funkiest band

1160
01:06:38.286 --> 01:06:40.371
might have had
a lot of left feet?

1161
01:06:41.831 --> 01:06:43.416
<i>- They all</i>
<i>could move to a degree.</i>

1162
01:06:43.458 --> 01:06:45.585
<i>but they were kind</i>
<i>of raggedy country.</i>

1163
01:06:45.668 --> 01:06:49.547
<i>and they weren't as polished</i>
<i>and theatrical</i>

1164
01:06:49.631 --> 01:06:51.424
<i>as I could make them.</i>

1165
01:06:51.466 --> 01:06:53.426
Because I wanted
them to be great.

1166
01:06:53.468 --> 01:06:55.053
I saw the greatness.

1167
01:06:55.136 --> 01:06:56.763
This is everybody.

1168
01:06:56.804 --> 01:06:58.223
Here we go.

1169
01:06:58.306 --> 01:07:00.558
One day. George is looking
at the front of the stage.

1170
01:07:00.600 --> 01:07:03.311
And he says. hey. Ralph.
come off the drums.

1171
01:07:03.394 --> 01:07:04.938
<i>Stand here next to Maurice.</i>

1172
01:07:04.979 --> 01:07:07.273
<i>Take this microphone.</i>
<i>and start singing.</i>

1173
01:07:07.357 --> 01:07:12.570
It was geometry and symmetry
and stuff like that.

1174
01:07:13.613 --> 01:07:16.115
<i>We didn't really</i>
<i>need two drummers.</i>

1175
01:07:16.199 --> 01:07:19.786
<i>and Freddie could go deeper.</i>

1176
01:07:19.869 --> 01:07:21.371
That's how I got out front.

1177
01:07:22.580 --> 01:07:25.041
<i>- It's about evolution.</i>
<i>you know?</i>

1178
01:07:25.124 --> 01:07:28.044
<i>I always had a lot of ideas.</i>

1179
01:07:28.127 --> 01:07:31.339
<i>We had started</i>
<i>to investigate. like. magic.</i>

1180
01:07:31.422 --> 01:07:33.800
The magic
of Doug Henning.

1181
01:07:37.303 --> 01:07:38.972
Doug Henning. at that time.
was the biggest

1182
01:07:39.013 --> 01:07:40.557
magician in the world.

1183
01:07:40.640 --> 01:07:41.641
<i>He had a show on NBC.</i>

1184
01:07:45.103 --> 01:07:46.646
<i>So Maurice calls him.</i>

1185
01:07:46.688 --> 01:07:49.899
Everyone wondered. Maurice.
are you that crazy?

1186
01:07:49.983 --> 01:07:52.986
<i>It was so out of the box.</i>

1187
01:07:53.027 --> 01:07:56.155
Magic. music. dance.

1188
01:07:56.239 --> 01:07:59.158
That was
a choreographic nightmare.

1189
01:07:59.200 --> 01:08:02.537
Somebody could have got
killed not doing things right.

1190
01:08:04.372 --> 01:08:07.125
<i>We rehearsed every day</i>
<i>for six months.</i>

1191
01:08:07.208 --> 01:08:09.127
<i>It was really</i>
<i>the first production</i>

1192
01:08:09.168 --> 01:08:11.212
<i>that an African American group</i>
<i>had really done.</i>

1193
01:08:11.296 --> 01:08:15.508
<i>putting all of those ideas</i>
<i>into one show.</i>

1194
01:08:15.550 --> 01:08:16.884
We didn't know
what kind of effect

1195
01:08:16.968 --> 01:08:19.262
it would have on the people.

1196
01:08:21.306 --> 01:08:23.641
<i>There's always a bit of fear</i>
<i>when you face the unknown.</i>

1197
01:08:28.896 --> 01:08:31.232
Dressing rooms are this way.

1198
01:08:31.316 --> 01:08:32.734
The stage is this way.

1199
01:08:34.736 --> 01:08:36.154
<i>I wanted to go see them.</i>

1200
01:08:36.237 --> 01:08:38.865
just to see if they
could pull that off.

1201
01:08:40.658 --> 01:08:42.869
<i>- Back in that day.</i>
<i>there were certain concerts</i>

1202
01:08:42.910 --> 01:08:44.162
<i>you had to go to.</i>

1203
01:08:44.245 --> 01:08:46.623
That show sold out.

1204
01:08:46.706 --> 01:08:48.583
<i>It was must-see.</i>

1205
01:08:50.543 --> 01:08:52.420
<i>I was there to photograph.</i>

1206
01:08:52.503 --> 01:08:56.049
Reese would let me crawl in...

1207
01:08:56.132 --> 01:08:59.385
<i>To be</i>
<i>as unobtrusive as possible.</i>

1208
01:08:59.427 --> 01:09:06.100
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1209
01:09:06.184 --> 01:09:10.605
<i>You had the anticipation--</i>

1210
01:09:10.688 --> 01:09:12.440
<i>20.000 people.</i>

1211
01:09:12.523 --> 01:09:16.319
And then. you know.
the lights go out.

1212
01:09:16.402 --> 01:09:18.655
Folks rush to their seats.

1213
01:09:22.241 --> 01:09:24.369
<i>Presenting</i>

1214
01:09:24.452 --> 01:09:29.248
<i>the mighty elders</i>
<i>of the universe.</i>

1215
01:09:29.332 --> 01:09:34.671
<i>Earth. Wind & Fire.</i>

1216
01:09:45.473 --> 01:09:47.934
It was one of the first
concerts I ever went to.

1217
01:09:48.017 --> 01:09:49.602
<i>These guys came out.</i>

1218
01:09:49.644 --> 01:09:52.313
and you're thinking.
what the heck?

1219
01:10:04.242 --> 01:10:06.703
And I was like. oh. shit.

1220
01:10:39.777 --> 01:10:42.655
<i>- I remember</i>
<i>just looking around the arena.</i>

1221
01:10:42.697 --> 01:10:46.325
It wasn't even a show.
It was just musical theater.

1222
01:10:46.367 --> 01:10:49.620
<i>It was just spectacular.</i>

1223
01:10:49.704 --> 01:10:53.040
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Oh. oh ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1224
01:10:54.375 --> 01:10:55.501
It was almost like a sermon.

1225
01:11:12.518 --> 01:11:13.895
