<i>Maurice needed a whole</i>
<i>different-sounding record.</i>

1612
01:30:51.655 --> 01:30:56.034
Maurice and I got together
through my wife.

1613
01:30:56.076 --> 01:30:58.662
Wanda. of The Emotions.

1614
01:30:58.745 --> 01:31:01.373
Maurice was digging
some of the things

1615
01:31:01.456 --> 01:31:05.710
that I was playing with
The Brothers Johnson.

1616
01:31:05.794 --> 01:31:09.631
Maurice came over to me.
and he said. hey. Wayne.

1617
01:31:09.714 --> 01:31:13.551
<i>you got any tunes</i>
<i>for the Fire?</i>

1618
01:31:13.635 --> 01:31:16.221
Reese and I were
going for hits.

1619
01:31:16.304 --> 01:31:17.806
So I gave him four songs.

1620
01:31:17.889 --> 01:31:20.183
and he decided
to cut three of them.

1621
01:31:20.266 --> 01:31:23.561
<i>one being "Let's Groove."</i>

1622
01:31:23.603 --> 01:31:27.065
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Let's groove tonight ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1623
01:31:27.148 --> 01:31:29.109
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Share the spice of life ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1624
01:31:31.611 --> 01:31:35.865
"Let's Groove" wasn't a true
Earth. Wind & Fire song.

1625
01:31:35.949 --> 01:31:38.743
<i>that metaphysical</i>
<i>kind of vibe.</i>

1626
01:31:38.785 --> 01:31:43.331
<i>It was just one tune to bridge</i>
<i>them over into the '80s.</i>

1627
01:31:43.415 --> 01:31:46.751
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ It's all right.
all right ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1628
01:31:46.835 --> 01:31:48.545
<i>- "Let's Groove"</i>
<i>was a hit record</i>

1629
01:31:48.628 --> 01:31:50.422
<i>that we needed at the time.</i>

1630
01:31:50.505 --> 01:31:51.756
We were relieved
because we said.

1631
01:31:51.798 --> 01:31:53.925
we made it in
on the 1-yard line. you know.

1632
01:31:53.967 --> 01:31:59.514
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Gonna tell you what
you can do with our love ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1633
01:31:59.597 --> 01:32:02.017
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ All right ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1634
01:32:02.100 --> 01:32:03.643
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Let you know. girl ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1635
01:32:03.727 --> 01:32:05.186
<i>- You're trying</i>
<i>to stay relevant.</i>

1636
01:32:05.270 --> 01:32:08.064
but. I mean. there were
some badass bands out there.

1637
01:32:08.148 --> 01:32:09.274
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ All right ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1638
01:32:09.315 --> 01:32:11.109
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ You will find</i>
<i>peace of mind ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1639
01:32:11.151 --> 01:32:14.529
Each decade brings
new music. new artists.

1640
01:32:14.612 --> 01:32:16.781
<i>new superstars.</i>

1641
01:32:16.823 --> 01:32:19.159
<i>Mike hit the home run</i>
<i>with "Thriller."</i>

1642
01:32:19.242 --> 01:32:21.619
<i>Lionel hit the home run</i>
<i>and. of course. Prince.</i>

1643
01:32:21.703 --> 01:32:27.292
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ We can boogie
on down now ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1644
01:32:27.333 --> 01:32:29.794
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Boogie on down ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1645
01:32:29.836 --> 01:32:32.964
<i>- We were</i>
<i>vying for our place.</i>

1646
01:32:33.048 --> 01:32:34.549
<i>Where are we</i>
<i>in the scheme of things?</i>

1647
01:32:34.632 --> 01:32:37.594
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ We boogie
on down. on down ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1648
01:32:37.677 --> 01:32:43.099
That magic. that combo.
it's very hard to keep

1649
01:32:43.183 --> 01:32:45.643
something like that going.

1650
01:32:45.727 --> 01:32:48.855
<i>Maurice was a private guy.</i>

1651
01:32:48.938 --> 01:32:53.151
<i>He didn't let me</i>
<i>see him sweat. but</i>

1652
01:32:53.193 --> 01:32:57.739
he had a lot of things
going on at one time.

1653
01:32:57.822 --> 01:32:58.990
<i>To the outside world.</i>

1654
01:32:59.032 --> 01:33:05.705
there was this positive
love image presented.

1655
01:33:05.789 --> 01:33:08.666
But to us. it was
totally different.

1656
01:33:08.750 --> 01:33:12.337
<i>Maurice was always</i>
<i>separated from everyone.</i>

1657
01:33:12.378 --> 01:33:15.131
<i>There was only certain people</i>
<i>that could do an interview.</i>

1658
01:33:15.173 --> 01:33:17.300
If you take a picture.
you must stand here.

1659
01:33:17.383 --> 01:33:19.260
just definite positions.

1660
01:33:19.344 --> 01:33:21.846
And there were things that
were done intentionally

1661
01:33:21.888 --> 01:33:23.681
to just make you feel small.

1662
01:33:26.351 --> 01:33:28.436
Gotta do it differently.

1663
01:33:28.520 --> 01:33:32.190
<i>- For one thing. we knew</i>
<i>we weren't getting paid right.</i>

1664
01:33:32.232 --> 01:33:34.109
<i>Yes. things were expensive.</i>

1665
01:33:34.192 --> 01:33:38.196
<i>but we were generating</i>
<i>millions of dollars</i>

1666
01:33:38.238 --> 01:33:42.867
and only making $2.500 a week.

1667
01:33:42.951 --> 01:33:47.580
<i>I think it was less than</i>
<i>some of the roadies.</i>

1668
01:33:47.664 --> 01:33:48.915
For the first eight years.

1669
01:33:48.998 --> 01:33:51.167
Maurice took
everybody's publishing.

1670
01:33:51.251 --> 01:33:54.045
<i>- My first royalty check.</i>
<i>Maurice handed it to me.</i>

1671
01:33:54.129 --> 01:33:56.714
<i>He said. here's</i>
<i>your royalties for the record.</i>

1672
01:33:56.756 --> 01:33:57.799
And I looked at Maurice.

1673
01:33:57.882 --> 01:34:00.093
It was like. what's this?

1674
01:34:01.553 --> 01:34:04.389
<i>- Maurice was very slow</i>
<i>to give up</i>

1675
01:34:04.472 --> 01:34:07.392
<i>any kind of credit to anybody.</i>

1676
01:34:07.433 --> 01:34:09.018
The whole damn band

1677
01:34:09.102 --> 01:34:10.728
should have gotten
co-production credit.

1678
01:34:10.770 --> 01:34:13.648
<i>but he had to be perceived</i>

1679
01:34:13.731 --> 01:34:17.277
<i>as the single champion</i>
<i>of the sound.</i>

1680
01:34:17.360 --> 01:34:18.945
<i>Some of the other guys</i>

1681
01:34:19.028 --> 01:34:20.613
<i>thought we deserved</i>
<i>better than that.</i>

1682
01:34:20.697 --> 01:34:22.866
and I'm inclined to agree.

1683
01:34:22.949 --> 01:34:25.618
<i>- There's no reason</i>
<i>to go through</i>

1684
01:34:25.702 --> 01:34:27.912
that kind of a treatment
without being paid.

1685
01:34:27.954 --> 01:34:29.581
If you're not making
any money.

1686
01:34:29.664 --> 01:34:32.208
why be there
and be treated that way?

1687
01:34:34.252 --> 01:34:35.920
<i>I never came back.</i>

1688
01:34:38.339 --> 01:34:43.303
<i>- The Phenix Horns left</i>
<i>to work with Phil Collins.</i>

1689
01:34:43.386 --> 01:34:45.638
<i>It was just bad blood.</i>

1690
01:34:45.722 --> 01:34:48.224
And then him and Al
fell out. and Al quit.

1691
01:34:50.935 --> 01:34:53.688
The party's gotta
end sometime. you know.

1692
01:34:57.275 --> 01:35:00.862
<i>- It was a big blow</i>
<i>because. after that.</i>

1693
01:35:00.945 --> 01:35:03.239
the band's sound changed.

1694
01:35:14.834 --> 01:35:17.754
<i>- The thing is is trying</i>
<i>to keep a band together</i>

1695
01:35:17.795 --> 01:35:21.007
<i>and stay commercial</i>
<i>but yet artistic.</i>

1696
01:35:21.090 --> 01:35:22.884
<i>It's a very hard thing to do.</i>

1697
01:35:22.967 --> 01:35:25.595
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ No self control ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1698
01:35:25.678 --> 01:35:29.641
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ A chain reaction
as my body lets go ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1699
01:35:29.724 --> 01:35:32.143
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ A strange kind of light ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1700
01:35:32.227 --> 01:35:36.105
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ The tempo takes me
and the circuit excites ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1701
01:35:36.189 --> 01:35:37.148
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Magnetic ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1702
01:35:37.190 --> 01:35:38.983
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ The rhythm
of a dangerous... ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1703
01:35:39.025 --> 01:35:43.780
<i>- The Earth. Wind & Fire</i>
<i>brand shifted.</i>

1704
01:35:43.863 --> 01:35:46.366
With all my heart.
I think that "Faces"

1705
01:35:46.449 --> 01:35:48.701
was the last great record.

1706
01:35:48.785 --> 01:35:51.246
<i>The rest of the stuff</i>
<i>is suspect.</i>

1707
01:35:51.329 --> 01:35:53.706
<i>- What is it about</i>
<i>"Raise!." "Powerlight."</i>

1708
01:35:53.790 --> 01:35:56.459
<i>and "Electric Universe"</i>
<i>that has you feeling</i>

1709
01:35:56.542 --> 01:35:57.877
that it's not up to par?

1710
01:35:57.961 --> 01:36:00.505
Maybe it's because
we had very little to do

1711
01:36:00.588 --> 01:36:02.382
with any of those records.

1712
01:36:04.467 --> 01:36:06.594
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ A new kind of beat ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1713
01:36:06.678 --> 01:36:08.846
<i>I found them unlistenable.</i>

1714
01:36:08.888 --> 01:36:12.517
Seemed to me to be Maurice
reaching for an audience.

1715
01:36:12.558 --> 01:36:14.352
<i>But it didn't have</i>
<i>that groove.</i>

1716
01:36:14.435 --> 01:36:15.812
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Suck you in ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1717
01:36:15.895 --> 01:36:17.772
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ You'll never last ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1718
01:36:17.855 --> 01:36:19.607
ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Step in the light tonight ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ

1719
01:36:19.691 --> 01:36:21.276
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Come make</i>
<i>the sparks ignite ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1720
01:36:21.359 --> 01:36:22.694
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Step in the light ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1721
01:36:22.735 --> 01:36:25.780
<i>- That time</i>
<i>had Maurice searching.</i>

1722
01:36:25.863 --> 01:36:27.949
You know. success
has many fathers.

1723
01:36:28.032 --> 01:36:29.867
but failure is an orphan.

1724
01:36:36.165 --> 01:36:39.544
I think the stress of all of
it was starting to get to him.

1725
01:36:39.627 --> 01:36:42.964
Beyond anything else.
he was fatigued.

1726
01:36:43.047 --> 01:36:44.674
<i>- Constantly touring</i>
<i>all the time</i>

1727
01:36:44.757 --> 01:36:46.926
<i>and then doing all</i>
<i>the other work. too.</i>

1728
01:36:47.010 --> 01:36:50.972
<i>I was always the one</i>
<i>who had to carry the load.</i>

1729
01:36:51.055 --> 01:36:53.391
<i>- He had decades</i>
<i>of emotional blockage.</i>

1730
01:36:53.433 --> 01:36:56.477
You push your feelings
down for only so long.

1731
01:36:56.561 --> 01:36:58.396
They have to go somewhere.

1732
01:36:58.438 --> 01:37:01.816
And if you don't let them out.
man. some shit can happen.

1733
01:37:09.198 --> 01:37:13.494
We were called
to a meeting at The Complex.

1734
01:37:13.578 --> 01:37:14.912
<i>We all gathered.</i>

1735
01:37:14.996 --> 01:37:17.248
<i>Maurice came down.</i>

1736
01:37:17.290 --> 01:37:21.002
<i>He said. guys. you know.</i>
<i>I've been thinking.</i>

1737
01:37:21.085 --> 01:37:23.588
<i>I wanna go my own way.</i>

1738
01:37:23.629 --> 01:37:27.008
And I think that

1739
01:37:27.091 --> 01:37:29.469
I'm gonna put Earth. Wind
& Fire on the back burner.

1740
01:37:32.305 --> 01:37:33.681
Are you kidding?

1741
01:37:33.765 --> 01:37:35.308
My heart sunk down to my toes.

1742
01:37:35.391 --> 01:37:38.436
I was like. Jesus.

1743
01:37:38.478 --> 01:37:41.564
<i>He said that. as of today.</i>

1744
01:37:41.647 --> 01:37:45.151
<i>we're going to</i>
<i>stop employment.</i>

1745
01:37:45.234 --> 01:37:50.073
<i>And we have to get our</i>
<i>wardrobe out of the lockers</i>

1746
01:37:50.156 --> 01:37:52.200
<i>because they were</i>
<i>gonna be sold.</i>

1747
01:37:55.244 --> 01:37:59.457
We were pretty much
in shock at that point.

1748
01:37:59.499 --> 01:38:03.252
<i>- I was upset</i>
<i>about the way it was done.</i>

1749
01:38:03.294 --> 01:38:06.839
You can't call a meeting
and say. okay. it's over

1750
01:38:06.923 --> 01:38:09.967
with no warning at all.

1751
01:38:10.051 --> 01:38:12.387
<i>- I don't think anybody</i>
<i>was as close</i>

1752
01:38:12.470 --> 01:38:15.473
<i>as Maurice and I were.</i>

1753
01:38:15.556 --> 01:38:19.811
<i>so it was definitely a shaker.</i>

1754
01:38:19.894 --> 01:38:21.396
But it was over.

1755
01:38:23.564 --> 01:38:26.067
<i>- Everybody just</i>
<i>kind of went their own way.</i>

1756
01:38:26.150 --> 01:38:28.861
<i>We were all estranged.</i>

1757
01:38:28.945 --> 01:38:30.822
My credit card bounced.

1758
01:38:30.863 --> 01:38:35.660
<i>Me and my wife. at that time.</i>
<i>panicked. sold the property.</i>

1759
01:38:35.701 --> 01:38:37.829
and moved to Denver.

1760
01:38:37.912 --> 01:38:39.831
I was on
a construction site.

1761
01:38:39.872 --> 01:38:43.709
I also was working
at a Federated stereo

1762
01:38:43.793 --> 01:38:48.089
on Sunset and La Brea.
selling stereo.

1763
01:38:48.172 --> 01:38:50.258
That was a tough period.

1764
01:38:50.341 --> 01:38:52.510
So yeah.

1765
01:38:52.552 --> 01:38:55.263
<i>- I'm sure it was devastating</i>
<i>to some of them.</i>

1766
01:38:57.098 --> 01:39:00.184
<i>But I had to let it go</i>
<i>at that point.</i>

1767
01:39:00.268 --> 01:39:04.605
I needed a break.
and I took a break. you know.

1768
01:39:04.689 --> 01:39:07.483
Yeah. I needed it.

1769
01:39:07.567 --> 01:39:10.027
<i>- These guys were</i>
<i>that family that he created.</i>

1770
01:39:10.111 --> 01:39:15.199
And he essentially did to them

1771
01:39:15.283 --> 01:39:18.286
what was done to him
when he was a child.

1772
01:39:20.288 --> 01:39:22.331
He left them before
they could leave him.

1773
01:39:24.542 --> 01:39:25.543
<i>He'd call me.</i>

1774
01:39:25.585 --> 01:39:30.089
And I said to him. you're
still holding on to the...

1775
01:39:30.173 --> 01:39:32.592
Non-forgiveness of what

1776
01:39:32.675 --> 01:39:33.676
your mother did to you.

1777
01:39:36.053 --> 01:39:40.057
You've got to release
in order for you

1778
01:39:40.099 --> 01:39:42.768
to be free
of what happened to you.

1779
01:39:42.852 --> 01:39:44.645
<i>And he couldn't do that.</i>

1780
01:39:46.314 --> 01:39:49.066
<i>- Breathe out</i>
<i>all of the separateness.</i>

1781
01:39:49.108 --> 01:39:51.986
<i>all of the feelings</i>
<i>of unworthiness.</i>

1782
01:39:52.069 --> 01:39:54.906
<i>all of the attachment</i>
<i>to your pain.</i>

1783
01:39:54.947 --> 01:39:59.035
<i>whether it's physical</i>
<i>or psychological.</i>

1784
01:39:59.076 --> 01:40:02.955
<i>Let the breath be</i>
<i>the transformation.</i>

1785
01:40:15.092 --> 01:40:17.762
Testing one. two.
Testing one. two.

1786
01:40:17.803 --> 01:40:19.347
- I'm good. right?
- Yeah. we're great.

1787
01:40:19.430 --> 01:40:20.598
You ready?

1788
01:40:20.640 --> 01:40:23.726
Hi. this is Maurice White
in Los Angeles.

1789
01:40:23.768 --> 01:40:27.104
Hope you enjoy
my new--do it again.

1790
01:40:27.188 --> 01:40:29.607
Hi. this is Maurice White
in Los Angeles.

1791
01:40:29.649 --> 01:40:33.277
Hope you enjoy my first
solo effort. "Stand By Me."

1792
01:40:33.361 --> 01:40:38.115
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ When the night has come ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1793
01:40:38.199 --> 01:40:41.202
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ And the land is dark ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1794
01:40:41.285 --> 01:40:47.416
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ And the moon</i>
<i>is the only light we see ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1795
01:40:47.500 --> 01:40:49.377
<i>- Maurice put a lot</i>
<i>into that record.</i>

1796
01:40:49.460 --> 01:40:52.088
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ No. I won't be afraid ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1797
01:40:52.171 --> 01:40:53.923
<i>But it didn't work.</i>

1798
01:40:54.006 --> 01:40:57.552
And I think the failure
really stung.

1799
01:41:00.096 --> 01:41:02.974
<i>- Philip Bailey</i>
<i>embarked on a solo career</i>

1800
01:41:03.015 --> 01:41:06.310
<i>without his former colleague.</i>

1801
01:41:06.352 --> 01:41:09.397
It was time to do
something else

1802
01:41:09.480 --> 01:41:13.317
and get a chance
to find out who I was.

1803
01:41:13.359 --> 01:41:17.113
<i>My solo career gave me</i>
<i>that autonomy</i>

1804
01:41:17.196 --> 01:41:19.657
<i>to play with</i>
<i>different musicians.</i>

1805
01:41:19.699 --> 01:41:22.910
I chose Phil Collins to work
with because the Phenix Horns

1806
01:41:22.994 --> 01:41:24.704
<i>were working with him.</i>

1807
01:41:26.289 --> 01:41:28.207
<i>ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ Easy lover ﾃ｢邃｢ﾂｪ</i>

1808
01:41:28.291 --> 01:41:30.418
<i>And I had a</i>
<i>across-the-board hit</i>

1809
01:41:30.501 --> 01:41:33.713
<i>with a song called</i>
<i>"Easy Lover."</i>

1810
01:41:33.796 --> 01:41:35.548
